  <title>Script Editor Shortcut Keys</title>

  <section>
    <title>Reference: Script Editor Shortcut Keys</title>

    <para>The GMAT Script Editor provides a user with text editor capabilities
    inside of the GMAT GUI. This article provides a listing of the current
    shortcut keys used in the Script Editor by release date. Shortcut key are
    subject to change in future releases. Check back to this article for
    Script Editor shortcut key updates.</para>

    <para>Would you like to take part in discussions for possible changes to
    the current shortcut keys? If so, visit the following forum topic:
	<link xlink:href="http://gmat.ed-pages.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=2&amp;t=107">Proposed
    Shortcut Keys inside GMAT (Text Fields)</link></para>

    <section>
      <title>2008-09-30 and 2007-12-10</title>

      <informaltable>
        <tgroup cols="2">
          <tbody>
            <row>
              <entry>Ctrl + C</entry>

              <entry>Copy</entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry>Ctrl + X</entry>

              <entry>Cut</entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry>Ctrl + V</entry>

              <entry>Paste</entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry>Ctrl + Z</entry>

              <entry>Undo</entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry>Ctrl + Y</entry>

              <entry>Redo</entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry>Ctrl + A</entry>

              <entry>Select All</entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry>Tab</entry>

              <entry>Move cursor to the next input field</entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry>Shift + Tab</entry>

              <entry>Move cursor to the previous input field</entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry>Ctrl + L</entry>

              <entry>Aligns highlighted text to the left (default
              alignment)</entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry>Ctrl + E</entry>

              <entry>Aligns highlighted text to the center (This alignment is
              not saved when the script is reloaded)</entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry>Ctrl + R</entry>

              <entry>Aligns highlighted text to the right (This alignment is
              not saved when the script is reloaded)</entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry>Ctrl + J</entry>

              <entry>Aligns highlighted text to justified left?? (This
              alignment is not saved when the script is reloaded)</entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry>Ctrl + track mouse scroll</entry>

              <entry>Enlarge/Decrease text size in script editor</entry>
            </row>
          </tbody>
        </tgroup>
      </informaltable>
    </section>

